                              </expan> (<locus from="17rb" to="18ra">17rb-18ra</locus>)</item>
                           <item>Texts II-IV</item>
                           <item>ም፡/ምል፡/ምልጣ፡ for ምልጣን፡</item>
                           <item>ተሣ፡ እ for ተሣሃለነ: እግዚኦ</item>
                           <item>ቅ፡ እ፡ ቅ፡ ኃ፡ ቅ፡ ሕ for ቅዱስ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ቅዱስ፡ ኃያል፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሕያው</item>
                           <item>መስተ፡/መስተብ፡ for መስተብቍዕ፡</item>
                           <item>ይትባ፡/ይትባረ፡ for ይትባረክ፡</item>
                           <item>መዝ፡/መዝሙ፡ for መዝሙር፡</item>
                           <item>ዘይእ፡ for ዘይእዜ፡</item>
                           <item>ሰላ፡ for ሰላም፡</item>
                           <item>ሃ፡ for ሃሌሉያ</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; title and incipit of daily readings of
                           Text I; refrains of Text I (written out fully or abbreviated); numbers of
                           Pss. in Text II; names of sections of antiphons and their abbreviations
                           (mǝlṭān and mazmur) in Text II; initial line of Text III; titles of Texts
                           IV and V; names of supplications, antiphons and chants, and their
                           abbreviations (e.g., mastabqʷǝʿ, mǝlṭān, mazmur, salām, ʾaryām) of Text
                           IV; names of feasts of Text IV; names of sections followed by feast names
                           (e.g., wāzemā za-masqal, wāzemā za-ʾarbaʿǝtu ʾǝnsǝsa) of Text IV; names
                           of antiphons and their abbreviations (e.g., māḥlet, mazmur, śalast,
                           salām, ba-5-tu, ʾabun, ʾaryām, ʾǝsma la-ʿālam, za-ʾamlākiya, za-yǝʾǝze,
                           yǝtbārak); names of other chants and their abbreviations (e.g., mǝlṭān,
                           mǝsbak, ʿǝzl); intratextual musical signs (e.g., ʿararat mäḥa, ḥaḍä, wäy,
                           läkä sǝ, qadāmi zema); elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic
                           numerals or their elements.
 
 Two lines (alternating with a
                           black line) on the incipit page of Texts I, IV and V.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
